    <text x="376" y="146" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13">domestic law stays intact each side</text>
    <text x="376" y="174" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13">Scope: limited to two countries</text>
    <text x="376" y="202" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13">Enforcement: SEC, CFTC, FCA, BoE joint work</text>
    <text x="376" y="242" fill="#fbbf24" font-size="13" font-weight="700">Pro: less political friction, flexible</text>
    <text x="376" y="266" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="13">Con: not legally binding; many past</text>
    <text x="376" y="290" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="13">dialogues of this kind fizzled out</text>
